-- Lesson 16: Generators
--
-- A function containing `yield` automatically becomes a generator
-- (JS function*). Each yield hands out one value; the caller can
-- iterate over them with for-in.

-- TODO: Make count-up yield 1, 2, ..., limit in order.
--       Hint: let i be 1, then while i le limit: yield i and i add be 1
fn count-up limit
  yield 0

for v in count-up[3]
  console.log[v]
